The paper deals with the complexity of Integer Linear Programming (ILP) and its tractable fragments, which are important in artificial intelligence. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with structural parameterizations of the constraint matrix within the framework of parameterized complexity. However, cs.CC is also a likely category, as the paper studies the complexity of ILP w.r.t. decompositional parameters. Finally, cs.AI and cs.LG are less likely categories, but they cannot be completely ruled out given the importance of ILP in artificial intelligence.
